      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried hoisting this into ctx.value, which all task runners share: report an incomplete error whenever the result is a still-evaluating vertex. That breaks legitimate uses — most ctx.value callers tolerate a partial value or report their own, better-contextualized incomplete errors. For example, builtin arguments regress (text/template.Execute on a not-yet-settled struct fails with \"value not yet known\" instead of evaluating), and incomplete-tolerant cases like builtins/all okIncompleteChild turn into errors; 79 eval sub-tests fail in total. Gating the generic check on the requested condition does not help either: only two callers request scalarValue, and the other one (processPatternConstraint) goes through evalState rather than ctx.value, so the gate would de facto select this one caller anyway.\n\nSo I kept the check here, where a permanent decision is made based on the value\u0027s kind, and extended the comment to record that reasoning.",
